970
01:34:56,669 --> 01:34:57,931
I'm fine. Why?

971
01:34:58,004 --> 01:34:59,904
You sound half-human.

972
01:35:00,340 --> 01:35:01,864
I am half-human.

973
01:35:05,578 --> 01:35:09,571
I was in your office when you
and Dr. Conrad were talking.

974
01:35:14,287 --> 01:35:15,879
Do you remember what you said?

975
01:35:16,756 --> 01:35:19,190
"I don't want to ruin it for him," you said.

976
01:35:22,095 --> 01:35:24,461
"I love him too much for that."

977
01:35:26,099 --> 01:35:27,088
You remember?

978
01:35:28,368 --> 01:35:29,232
No.

979
01:35:33,740 --> 01:35:36,868
I swore that one day
I was going to say it to your face.

980
01:35:42,849 --> 01:35:44,714
Come on, you have to look at me.

981
01:35:46,853 --> 01:35:49,253
Are we going to do this the hard way?

982
01:35:58,665 --> 01:36:00,462
I love you, too, Marcus.

983
01:36:15,948 --> 01:36:17,472
What's our plan?

984
01:36:32,932 --> 01:36:34,263
<i>Stage 3.</i>

985
01:36:44,043 --> 01:36:47,535
<i>Good morning, ladies and gentlemen,
and welcome to Golden, Colorado...</i>

986
01:36:47,613 --> 01:36:52,050
<i>... site of the third and final stage
of a race they call the Hell of the West.</i>

987
01:36:52,185 --> 01:36:54,881
<i>Looks like we're in
for a great day here today.</i>

988
01:37:06,132 --> 01:37:11,160
<i>Before we get started, I'd like to introduce
the main contenders in this competition.</i>

989
01:37:11,237 --> 01:37:13,797
<i>Beginning with the rider
in third place overall...</i>

990
01:37:13,873 --> 01:37:17,673
<i>... 11 seconds behind the leader,
David Sommers.</i>

991
01:37:19,879 --> 01:37:22,746
<i>In second place overall,
from the Soviet Union...</i>

992
01:37:22,815 --> 01:37:26,216
<i>... only two seconds behind the leader,
Sergei Belov.</i>

993
01:37:29,055 --> 01:37:33,185
<i>And ladies and gentlemen,
last year's winner of the Hell of the West...</i>

994
01:37:33,259 --> 01:37:36,786
<i>... the race leader today going into
the third and final stage...</i>

995
01:37:37,163 --> 01:37:39,222
<i>... Barry "the Cannibal" Muzzin.</i>

996
01:37:44,303 --> 01:37:46,897
<i>We'rejust minutes from the start
of the competition.</i>

997
01:37:46,973 --> 01:37:49,999
<i>All caravan drivers,
please report to your vehicles.</i>

998
01:37:50,076 --> 01:37:52,874
<i>All officials, please report to your vehicles.</i>

999
01:38:57,443 --> 01:39:00,606
<i>Here's a surprise.
The Russians are starting things early.</i>

1000
01:39:00,680 --> 01:39:04,980
<i>Belov is sending a teammate up the road,
forcing the others to do the chasing.</i>

1001
01:39:05,051 --> 01:39:08,919
<i>That will take some of the sap out of them
if they're not able to hold the pace.</i>

1002
01:39:08,988 --> 01:39:13,186
<i>The weaker ones will get burned off and
won't be able to make the climbs.</i>

1003
01:39:13,259 --> 01:39:15,557
<i>Over 100 miles to go and the Russians...</i>

1004
01:39:15,628 --> 01:39:18,461
<i>... are really making things pop
right off the bat.</i>

1005
01:39:18,865 --> 01:39:23,302
<i>Belov must have a lot of confidence in
his ability to start a breakaway so early...</i>

1006
01:39:23,402 --> 01:39:25,063
<i>... in a race like this.</i>

1007
01:39:30,877 --> 01:39:33,107
It's no fun up front, is it?

1008
01:39:45,124 --> 01:39:47,092
I must be hallucinating.

1009
01:39:48,895 --> 01:39:50,590
That looks like Randolph.

1010
01:39:52,565 --> 01:39:53,793
It is Randolph.

1011
01:39:53,866 --> 01:39:55,356
Who's Randolph?

1012
01:40:00,139 --> 01:40:01,504
Sarah, pull over.

1013
01:40:11,684 --> 01:40:13,117
Mr. Sommers, don't!

1014
01:40:29,035 --> 01:40:31,060
Do you want to go with us?

1015
01:40:36,509 --> 01:40:37,601
Go around.

1016
01:40:37,910 --> 01:40:40,504
We'll follow you.
Come on, let's go, Randolph.

1017
01:40:43,516 --> 01:40:44,608
You must be Sarah.

1018
01:40:44,684 --> 01:40:46,811
- Yes. Mrs. Sommers.
- How do you do?

1019
01:40:47,587 --> 01:40:49,282
- Hi, I'm Becky.
- Hi.

1020
01:40:51,457 --> 01:40:52,947
Okay, let's go.

1021
01:41:06,072 --> 01:41:10,008
<i>Golden to Mount Evans race is the third
and final stage of the Hell of the West.</i>

1022
01:41:10,076 --> 01:41:14,740
<i>It's also the most difficult. It starts at
the Coors Brewery in Golden, Colorado...</i>

1023
01:41:14,814 --> 01:41:18,944
<i>... and begins a spectacular climb
over 6,000 feet into the Rocky Mountains...</i>

1024
01:41:19,085 --> 01:41:21,713
<i>... finishing nearly 12,000 feet
above sea level.</i>

1025
01:41:21,787 --> 01:41:25,348
<i>And that's over the highest paved road
in North America.</i>

1026
01:41:25,691 --> 01:41:28,660
<i>Not many of these cyclists
have ever raced at this altitude.</i>

1027
01:41:28,728 --> 01:41:32,027
<i>In Europe, for instance, the courses
through the Alps are much lower.</i>

1028
01:41:32,098 --> 01:41:33,497
<i>It's a torturous course.</i>

1029
01:41:33,566 --> 01:41:37,434
<i>Even the fittest athletes can't get
enough air to maintain a normal speed.</i>

1030
01:41:44,276 --> 01:41:46,676
Notice anything unusual, Randolph?

1031
01:41:47,413 --> 01:41:49,108
Yeah, I have jet lag.

1032
01:41:50,950 --> 01:41:52,918
Hardly any black riders out there.

1033
01:41:53,586 --> 01:41:54,644
Think about it.

1034
01:41:54,720 --> 01:41:56,415
I don't have a bicycle, Dad.

1035
01:41:56,489 --> 01:41:58,218
Your birthday's coming up.

1036
01:42:01,994 --> 01:42:03,859
I want a bowling ball.

1037
01:42:07,900 --> 01:42:10,130
I'm still here, Belov.

1038
01:42:10,202 --> 01:42:11,965
Right on your red ass.

1039
01:42:12,038 --> 01:42:13,767
Think about this, Belov:

1040
01:42:13,839 --> 01:42:17,104
I'm behind you,
but I'm really two seconds ahead.

1041
01:42:17,410 --> 01:42:19,605
Are you nuts?
He doesn't understand English.

1042
01:42:19,679 --> 01:42:20,703
He understands.

1043
01:42:21,280 --> 01:42:22,577
Don't you, Belov?

1044
01:42:23,182 --> 01:42:26,549
You know why you won the Olympics?
Because I wasn't there.

1045
01:42:27,620 --> 01:42:28,985
Well, now I'm here.

1046
01:42:29,255 --> 01:42:31,416
Only I'm not here. I'm two seconds ahead.

1047
01:42:33,759 --> 01:42:35,852
He does understand English.

1048
01:42:56,348 --> 01:42:57,542
Up, Dave. Up.

1049
01:42:59,385 --> 01:43:00,374
Up, Dave.

1050
01:43:00,853 --> 01:43:01,945
That a boy.

1051
01:43:29,849 --> 01:43:31,009
Get him, Belov.

1052
01:43:31,083 --> 01:43:32,914
You go get him.

1053
01:43:47,133 --> 01:43:51,399
<i>Ten miles to go and David Sommers
is trying to steal this race from them.</i>

1054
01:43:51,537 --> 01:43:55,633
<i>He's been very aggressive this last mile,
forcing them to chase very hard.</i>

1055
01:43:55,708 --> 01:44:00,702
<i>These last few miles many riders will drop
as the lack of oxygen grows more severe.</i>

1056
01:44:00,913 --> 01:44:02,346
He's going all out early.

1057
01:44:02,414 --> 01:44:03,745
Should I pull over and wait?

1058
01:44:03,816 --> 01:44:07,445
No. Let's go up to the finish line.
It's his race, let him ride it.

1059
01:44:21,967 --> 01:44:23,730
Here we go, Sommers.

1060
01:44:54,767 --> 01:44:56,359
Okay, we got him.

1061
01:44:58,404 --> 01:45:01,737
Just sit back and you've got second
locked up. Okay?

1062
01:45:02,508 --> 01:45:03,532
Okay.

1063
01:45:21,126 --> 01:45:22,058
Shit!

1064
01:45:36,542 --> 01:45:39,943
I gave you a chance, Sommers.
Now all bets are off.

1065
01:46:19,919 --> 01:46:23,013
<i>It's David Sommers in the lead,
coming around the corner.</i>

1066
01:46:23,088 --> 01:46:25,147
<i>But even if he crosses the line first...</i>

1067
01:46:25,224 --> 01:46:28,751
<i>... Muzzin still has
an 11-second time advantage overall.</i>

1068
01:46:28,861 --> 01:46:32,388
<i>If Muzzin crosses the line
less than 11 seconds after Sommers...</i>

1069
01:46:32,498 --> 01:46:35,729
<i>... Muzzin will still be the winner
of the Hell of the West.</i>

1070
01:47:21,580 --> 01:47:24,481
<i>Sommers is finished.
He'll become the overall winner...</i>

1071
01:47:24,550 --> 01:47:28,145
<i>... if Muzzin doesn't cross the finish line
in the next 11 seconds.</i>

1072
01:47:44,903 --> 01:47:46,370
<i>Muzzin didn't make it.</i>

1073
01:47:46,438 --> 01:47:48,770
<i>David Sommers wins the final stage...</i>

1074
01:47:49,208 --> 01:47:52,268
<i>... and clinches the overall victory
in the Hell of the West.</i>

1075
01:47:52,344 --> 01:47:54,938
<i>A fantastic performance
by this young newcomer.</i>

1076
01:47:55,014 --> 01:47:58,575
<i>He has beaten the veterans this year
and made quite a name for himself.</i>

1077
01:47:58,650 --> 01:48:01,118
<i>Young David Sommers, a fantasticjob!</i>

1078
01:48:01,186 --> 01:48:04,417
<i>Let's give all these riders
a big round of applause as they come in.</i>

1079
01:48:04,490 --> 01:48:06,219
<i>What a finish here today!</i>

1080
01:48:13,599 --> 01:48:15,499
Mrs. Sommers, would you come up?

1081
01:48:15,567 --> 01:48:17,159
How about some smiles?

1082
01:48:22,674 --> 01:48:23,663
Next year.

1083
01:49:08,554 --> 01:49:09,953
Come on, look over here.

1084
01:49:11,190 --> 01:49:13,988
Come on, give us a smile.
Over here. Look out.

1085
01:49:14,059 --> 01:49:15,549
That's it. Picture, please.

1086
01:49:15,627 --> 01:49:17,390
That's it, that's it. Thank you.

